{"BUOY":[{"def":"To keep from sinking in a fluid, as in water or air; to keep afloat; -- with up.","pos":""},{"def":"To support or sustain; to preserve from sinking into ruin or despondency.","pos":""}],"BUOYAGE":[{"def":"Buoys, taken collectively; a series of buoys, as for the guidance of vessels into or out of port; the providing of buoys.","pos":""}],"BUOYANCY":[{"def":"The upward pressure exerted upon a floating body by a fluid, which is equal to the weight of the body; hence, also, the weight of a floating body, as measured by the volume of fluid displaced.","pos":""}],"BUOYANT":[{"def":"Having the quality of rising or floating in a fluid; tending to rise or float; as, iron is buoyant in mercury.","pos":""},{"def":"Bearing up, as a fluid; sustaining another body by being specifically heavier.","pos":""}]}